<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-16 19:40:01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> political </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Bush Sets Record for Fund Raising </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
                      *Associated Press Writer-    	
</P>
<P>
	SEATTLE (AP) -- The Seattle Mariners' bats have been silent for  
days at Safeco Field, but Republican presidential front-runner 
George W. Bush hit the political equivalent of a grand slam 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	The Texas governor, whose campaign treasury is closing in on the  
$60 million mark, a record, lent his starpower and fund-raising 
prowess to Sen. Slade Gorton, the state GOP and the National 
Republican Senatorial Committee. 
</P>
<P>
	The event, the first political event staged in America's newest  
and most expensive ballpark, raised more than $400,000, the largest 
single fund-raising event in Washington state history. 
</P>
<P>
	Bush's senior advisers said it's part of a new strategy of  
cementing his relations with congressional incumbents -- the very 
ones he has criticized generically in recent days -- and with GOP 
organizations in key battleground states. 
</P>
<P>
	``I like to help my friends,'' Bush said in an interview.  
</P>
<P>
	Aides said Bush has been swamped for months with requests and  
that after the bulk of his own fund-raising was completed, the 
governor decided to work in some of the events. 
</P>
<P>
	As the Iowa caucuses and New Hampshire primary draw nearer, he  
will have to concentrate on his own race more, his political 
strategists said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	``There is a benefit for me to do this,'' Bush said. ``It will  
help me a lot, if I am elected president, to have my friends in the 
House and in the Senate and in governors' mansions all across this 
great land. I'm asked a lot (to do campaign appearances and 
fund-raising), and I will do what I can.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Republicans haven't carried Washington in the past three  
presidential elections. Bush's father, former President George 
Bush, lost the state in both 1988 and 1992. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's just about time to break that streak,'' Bush told about  
400 people at the Safeco Field event. He told reporters he thinks 
his platform -- including education, free trade, a strong military 
and sensible environmental controls -- will resonate with Washington 
voters. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's a little early to tell what the dynamics are going to be  
for the general election, but my political antennae tell me I have 
a good chance. There is a certain disgruntlement with the status 
quo. 
</P>
<P>
	Bush fans paid $1,000 and up to dine on salmon, salad and wine,  
and hear speeches from Bush and Gorton. It was called a ``grand 
slam'' event -- and the setting was appropriate. 
</P>
<P>
	Tables, set up on the outfield, were covered with linen  
tablecloths, china and pots of flowers. The speeches were broadcast 
on giant screens on the Mariners' scoreboard. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW19991016.0024 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-16 12:07:01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> international </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Basque Novelist Honored in Spain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BARCELONA, Spain (AP) -- A 25-year-old Basque author has been  
awarded Spain's highest literary award for the story of a woman 
searching for her roots after her family moves to a new town, 
organizers said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Laura Espido Freire was awarded the Planeta publishing house  
prize Friday for her third novel, ``Frozen Peaches.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Espido Freire's work was chosen from 377 works and will be  
published by Planeta. 
</P>
<P>
	Her two previous novels, ``Ireland'' and ``Where It's Always  
October,'' were both highly praised by literary critics in Spain. 
</P>
<P>
	The 48th annual Planeta prize included a cash award equaling  
$312,500. 
</P>
<P>
	Previous winners of the Planeta prize include Uruguayan writer  
Carmen Posadas in 1998 with ``Minor Disgraces,'' and Spanish Nobel 
prize winner Camilo Jose Cela in 1994 for his work ``Saint Andrew's 
Cross.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW19991016.0025 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-16 12:07:01 </DATE_TIME>
