<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Four Students Killed in Car Wreck </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	GRAND HAVEN, Mich. (AP) -- Four high school freshmen riding in a  
stolen car were killed early Saturday when the vehicle struck a 
tree, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
	The teen-agers were not wearing seat belts and died at the scene  
of the crash about 12:50 a.m. near this western Michigan community, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
	Michigan State Police identified the victims as driver John  
Mogielski, and passengers Ryan Lyles, Adam Bennett and David 
Morgan. Morgan was 15, the others 14. 
</P>
<P>
	Schools Superintendent Rick Kent described the mood among their  
classmates as ``one of shock when you have a tragedy of this 
magnitude.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``There's tremendous sadness, tremendous feeling for the parents  
and the families of these four young people,'' he said. ``All four 
were very sociable, and they had a wide circle of friends.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Ottawa County sheriff's officials said the four were occupants  
of a car stolen from an area residence. The crash happened while 
the vehicle was traveling at a high rate of speed, the sheriff's 
office said in a statement. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
