<HEADLINE> 49ers Receiver Owens Out Sunday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SANTA CLARA, Calif. (AP) -- San Francisco 49ers wide receiver  
Terrell Owens will miss Sunday's game against the Carolina Panthers 
with a high ankle sprain that forced him to spend part of the past 
week in a walking cast. 
</P>
<P>
	The 49ers said Owens, who had been listed as questionable for  
the game, was ruled out after tests were performed Saturday morning 
on the ankle. 
</P>
<P>
	Quarterback Steve Young will miss his third straight game as he  
continues to recover from his fourth concussion over the last three 
years. 
  	   	
