<HEADLINE> Lucy Lawless Has Baby Boy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- ``Xena: Warrior Princess'' Lucy Lawless and  
husband Rob Tapert, the TV show's executive producer, have a new 
baby warrior. 
</P>
<P>
	Eight-pound, 13-ounce Julius Robert Bay Tapert was born Saturday  
morning in New Zealand, said Leah Krantzler, the actress' Los 
Angeles spokeswoman. 
</P>
<P>
	``Mom, dad, big sister Daisy and baby are all doing well,'' Ms.  
Krantzler said. 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. Lawless, star of the popular action-adventure TV series, was  
taking a regularly scheduled production hiatus. ``Xena'' resumes 
filming next month. 
</P>
<P>
	On the show, in its fifth season of national syndication, Xena's  
also pregnant. 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. Lawless, 31, and Tapert, 44, were married in March 1998.  
Daisy, 11, is Ms. Lawless' daughter from a previous marriage. 
  	   	
</P>
