<HEADLINE> Crop Insurance System Facts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Facts about the federally insured crop insurance system:  
</P>
<P>
	Number of policies sold this year: 1.84 million, up 5 percent  
from 1998. (The Agriculture Department offered discounts this year 
to encourage sales.) 
</P>
<P>
	Acreage covered: 198 million acres, up 9.3 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	Premiums collected: $2.3 billion, up 25 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	Estimated losses this year: $2.2 billion, with largest in Texas  
($260 million), North Dakota ($215 million) and North Carolina 
($213 million). Indiana, home state of the Senate Agriculture 
Committee chairman, Republican Richard Lugar, will have $45.6 
million in losses. 
</P>
<P>
	------	 
</P>
<P>
	Source: Agriculture Department's Risk Management Agency  
  	   	
</P>
