<HEADLINE> Artax Sets Record at Belmont </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Artax set a Belmont Park track record for six  
furlongs when he posted a 6 1/2-length victory in the $250,000 Forest 
Hills handicap Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Good and Tough finished second of seven another 1 1/2 lengths ahead  
of Intidab. 
</P>
<P>
	Artax's time of 1:07:3 was one-fifth faster than the previous  
mark set by Groovy on June 21, 1987. 
</P>
<P>
	It was Artex's second track record this year. He holds the  
Aqueduct track mark for seven furlongs in 1:20 in the Carter 
handicap on May 2. 
</P>
<P>
	It was the third win in fourteen starts this year for the  
4-year-old colt by Marquetry from the Apalachee mare, Raging 
Apalachee. 
</P>
<P>
	Artax earned $150,000 and returned $5.70, $3.30 and $2.70. Good  
and Tough paid $5.30 and $4.10 and Intidab was $3.40 to show. 
</P>
<P>
	Middlesex Drive led from the start and posted a 1 1/2-length  
victory in the 19th running of the $250,000 Kelso Handicap. 
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by Shane Sellers, Middlesex Drive went one mile in 1:35:2  
to earn $150,000 for C. Steven Duncker. It was the third win in 
seven starts this year for the 4-year-old colt. 
</P>
<P>
	Divide and Conquer was second of ten 3 1/2 lengths ahead of Wised  
Up. 
</P>
<P>
	Middlesex Drive returned $8.80, $5.00 and $3.40. Divide and  
Conquer paid $7.90 and $5.50 and Wised Up was 7.40 to show. 
  	   	
