<HEADLINE> Blackhawks' Dumont Injured </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PITTSBURGH (AP) -- Chicago Blackhawks forward Jean-Pierre Dumont  
left the ice on a stretcher in the third period of Saturday night's 
game against the Pittsburgh Penguins after he was hit by defenseman 
Darius Kasparaitis. 
</P>
<P>
	Dumont was injured 5:04 into the third period when he was caught  
on the chin by Kasparaitis' elbow near the boards as both players 
were skating toward the puck. Dumont was prone on the ice as 
several of his teammates went after Kasparaitis. 
</P>
<P>
	Dumont appeared to be conscious and talking to teammates as he  
was attended to by medical personnel. His neck was immobolized with 
a brace before he was wheeled off the ice. 
</P>
<P>
	Referees Paul Devorski and Brad Watson gave Kasparaitis a  
five-minute major penalty for elbowing and a game misconduct. 
Kasparaitis was playing his first game after missing training camp 
in a contract dispute. 
</P>
<P>
	Dumont, 21, is in his second NHL season with Chicago.  
  	   	
</P>
