<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Cops Probe Injury of Disabled Man </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PORTLAND, Ore. (AP) -- Police are investigating allegations that  
officers injured a mentally retarded Ukrainian immigrant after 
mistaking him for a burglary suspect. 
</P>
<P>
	The department's internal affairs division opened the probe  
Friday, said Detective Sgt. Cheryl Kanzler. 
</P>
<P>
	Pavel Guzenko, 36, was carting firewood to his relatives Tuesday  
night when officers investigating a report of a stolen wheelbarrow 
attempted to question him. 
</P>
<P>
	``Two female officers responded, stopped a man they saw with a  
wheelbarrow, and that's when things went bad,'' Ms. Kanzler said. 
She did not identify the officers. 
</P>
<P>
	The officers issued several orders to Guzenko, who does not  
understand English. Witnesses said the officers then jumped 
Guzenko, leaving the right side of his face badly scraped. 
</P>
<P>
	``He told me he was trying to tell them in Russian, `I'm  
sorry,''' said his sister-in-law, Tanya Guzenko. 
</P>
<P>
	Relatives later took Guzenko to an emergency room. Blood was  
found in his urine, suggesting he might have suffered internal 
injuries, said the family's lawyer, Gary Lau. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
